The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Saturday, March 24, 2007

 Video theatre

 Sottor/Uttor and 67-72, a durational diptych on the history of the Maoist movement in India by Santanu Bose and Debalina, at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 6.30 pm.

 Film fest, stamps, music

 Screening and discussion on a series of documentaries Gadia Lohar: A Life and Livelihood in Question and Flight of Distress at Seagull Bookstore, 3 pm.

 Japanese Film Festival at Rotary Sadan, 2 pm. Today: The Story of Jiro and Cherish His Smile. 

 An exhibition of postage stamps and memorabilia on cricket at City Centre, 10.30 am to 9 pm. 

 Indian classical vocal concert at the Calcutta School of Music, 7 pm. 

